The course covers topics that define the field of molecular ecology and systematics; basic ethics in animal research, major theoretical topics, various genetic markers and scientific methods used to solve scientific and applied problems in molecular ecology and systematics, but also in related fields such as animal and human healthcare.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course is intended to provide a useful basic background in molecular ecology and systematics and introduce possibilities for their practical application in various fields of biology, including nature conservation, but also in animal and human healthcare. Up to date theoretical and methodological issues will be discussed.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Following the course, student has acquired necessary theorethical knowledge in molecular ecology and systematics and is able to understand and address a multitude of scientific and applied problems with different approaches in molecular ecology and systematics.
